Harold was silent with admiration and respect.
Thy brother, continued Mr. Hammond, was not
like other boys. At times nothing could move himhe
would sit, moping, for days and days, under that old
tree, where we turned offHarold remembered itit
was very grand and beautifulat others, nothing could
