he was at rest. Never shall I forget the deep and
sweet composure of his manner, at the time. It was so
unlike himthat it seemed little else than a miraculous
quieting of his soul, by the hand of his Makerpressing
upon its tidesand lulling its currents. There were no
intermittent flashesno inquietude, and restlessness of
movement in him, after this. All was calm, collected,
and observant, as of one, who is at peace with all the
world, without, and prepared for every thing
within
.
